text_answer.content: The explanations in the fill-in section need to be more precise.  For example, "amounting" is described as a participle only.  It is a present particle that is functioning as the finite verb in the sentence becase it is accompanied by an auxiliary verb "was", which makes it a past progressive tense.  In the synonym/antonym exercise, the correct answer for each item is the word that appears in the word bank.  If students have access to the word bank, they don't need to differentiate between definition.  Even if students do not have access to the word bank, only the words from the word bank should appear as answer choices because this would provide added exposure to the target words.
